description: Fetch attributes of a rule set.

parameters.name: RuleSetId
parameters.description: The identifier of an existing rule set to be retrieved.

nested_items.name: CreatedDate
nested_items.description: The date of when then rule set was created.

nested_items.name: LastModificationDate
nested_items.description: The date of when the rule set was last modified.

nested_items.name: RuleSetArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the rule set resource.

nested_items.name: RuleSetId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the rule set resource.

nested_items.name: RuleSetName
nested_items.description: A user-friendly name for the rule set resource.

nested_items.name: Rules
nested_items.description: The rules contained in the rule set.

nested_items.name: Actions
nested_items.description: The list of actions to execute when the conditions match the incoming email, and none of the 'unless conditions' match.

nested_items.name: AddHeader
nested_items.description: This action adds a header. This can be used to add arbitrary email headers.

nested_items.name: HeaderName
nested_items.description: The name of the header to add to an email. The header must be prefixed with 'X-'. Headers are added regardless of whether the header name pre-existed in the email.

nested_items.name: HeaderValue
nested_items.description: The value of the header to add to the email.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the specified archive has been deleted.

nested_items.name: TargetArchive
nested_items.description: The identifier of the archive to send the email to.

nested_items.name: DeliverToMailbox
nested_items.description: This action delivers an email to a WorkMail mailbox.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the mailbox ARN is no longer valid.

nested_items.name: MailboxArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of a WorkMail organization to deliver the email to.

nested_items.name: RoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an IAM role to use to execute this action. The role must have access to the workmail:DeliverToMailbox API.

nested_items.name: DeliverToQBusiness
nested_items.description: This action delivers an email to an Amazon Q Business application for ingestion into its knowledge base.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the specified application has been deleted or the role lacks necessary permissions to call the qbusiness:BatchPutDocument API.

nested_items.name: ApplicationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon Q Business application instance where the email content will be delivered.

nested_items.name: IndexId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the knowledge base index within the Amazon Q Business application where the email content will be stored and indexed.

nested_items.name: RoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM Role to use while delivering to Amazon Q Business. This role must have access to the qbusiness:BatchPutDocument API for the given application and index.

nested_items.name: PublishToSns
nested_items.description: This action publishes the email content to an Amazon SNS topic.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, specified SNS topic has been deleted or the role lacks necessary permissions to call the sns:Publish API.

nested_items.name: Encoding
nested_items.description: The encoding to use for the email within the Amazon SNS notification. The default value is UTF-8. Use BASE64 if you need to preserve all special characters, especially when the original message uses a different encoding format.

nested_items.name: PayloadType
nested_items.description: The expected payload type within the Amazon SNS notification. CONTENT attempts to publish the full email content with 20KB of headers content. HEADERS extracts up to 100KB of header content to include in the notification, email content will not be included to the notification. The default value is CONTENT.

nested_items.name: RoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM Role to use while writing to Amazon SNS. This role must have access to the sns:Publish API for the given topic.

nested_items.name: TopicArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon SNS Topic to which notification for the email received will be published.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the specified relay has been deleted.

nested_items.name: MailFrom
nested_items.description: This action specifies whether to preserve or replace original mail from address while relaying received emails to a destination server.

nested_items.name: Relay
nested_items.description: The identifier of the relay resource to be used when relaying an email.

nested_items.name: ReplaceRecipient
nested_items.description: The action replaces certain or all recipients with a different set of recipients.

nested_items.name: ReplaceWith
nested_items.description: This action specifies the replacement recipient email addresses to insert.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the caller does not have the permissions to call the sendRawEmail API.

nested_items.name: RoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the role to use for this action. This role must have access to the ses:SendRawEmail API.

nested_items.name: WriteToS3
nested_items.description: This action writes the MIME content of the email to an S3 bucket.

nested_items.name: ActionFailurePolicy
nested_items.description: A policy that states what to do in the case of failure. The action will fail if there are configuration errors. For example, the specified the bucket has been deleted.

nested_items.name: RoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM Role to use while writing to S3. This role must have access to the s3:PutObject, kms:Encrypt, and kms:GenerateDataKey APIs for the given bucket.

nested_items.name: S3Bucket
nested_items.description: The bucket name of the S3 bucket to write to.

nested_items.name: S3Prefix
nested_items.description: The S3 prefix to use for the write to the s3 bucket.

nested_items.name: S3SseKmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The KMS Key ID to use to encrypt the message in S3.

nested_items.name: Conditions
nested_items.description: The conditions of this rule. All conditions must match the email for the actions to be executed. An empty list of conditions means that all emails match, but are still subject to any 'unless conditions'

nested_items.name: BooleanExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to a boolean expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Analyzer
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an Add On.

nested_items.name: ResultField
nested_items.description: The returned value from an Add On.

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: The boolean type representing the allowed attribute types for an email.

nested_items.name: IsInAddressList
nested_items.description: The structure representing the address lists and address list attribute that will be used in evaluation of boolean expression.

nested_items.name: AddressLists
nested_items.description: The address lists that will be used for evaluation.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: The email attribute that needs to be evaluated against the address list.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The matching operator for a boolean condition expression.

nested_items.name: DmarcExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to a DMARC policy expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The operator to apply to the DMARC policy of the incoming email.

nested_items.name: Values
nested_items.description: The values to use for the given DMARC policy operator. For the operator EQUALS, if multiple values are given, they are evaluated as an OR. That is, if any of the given values match, the condition is deemed to match. For the operator NOT_EQUALS, if multiple values are given, they are evaluated as an AND. That is, only if the email's DMARC policy is not equal to any of the given values, then the condition is deemed to match.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: IpExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to an IP address expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: The attribute of the email to evaluate.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The operator to evaluate the IP address.

nested_items.name: Values
nested_items.description: The IP CIDR blocks in format 'x.y.z.w/n' (eg 10.0.0.0/8) to match with the email's IP address. For the operator CIDR_MATCHES, if multiple values are given, they are evaluated as an OR. That is, if the IP address is contained within any of the given CIDR ranges, the condition is deemed to match. For NOT_CIDR_MATCHES, if multiple CIDR ranges are given, the condition is deemed to match if the IP address is not contained in any of the given CIDR ranges.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: NumberExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to a number expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: An email attribute that is used as the number to evaluate.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The operator for a numeric condition expression.

nested_items.name: Value
nested_items.description: The value to evaluate in a numeric condition expression.

nested_items.name: StringExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to a string expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Analyzer
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an Add On.

nested_items.name: ResultField
nested_items.description: The returned value from an Add On.

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: The email attribute to evaluate in a string condition expression.

nested_items.name: MimeHeaderAttribute
nested_items.description: The email MIME X-Header attribute to evaluate in a string condition expression.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The matching operator for a string condition expression.

nested_items.name: Values
nested_items.description: The string(s) to be evaluated in a string condition expression. For all operators, except for NOT_EQUALS, if multiple values are given, the values are processed as an OR. That is, if any of the values match the email's string using the given operator, the condition is deemed to match. However, for NOT_EQUALS, the condition is only deemed to match if none of the given strings match the email's string.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: VerdictExpression
nested_items.description: The condition applies to a verdict expression passed in this field.

nested_items.name: Analyzer
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an Add On.

nested_items.name: ResultField
nested_items.description: The returned value from an Add On.

nested_items.name: Attribute
nested_items.description: The email verdict attribute to evaluate in a string verdict expression.

nested_items.name: Operator
nested_items.description: The matching operator for a verdict condition expression.

nested_items.name: Values
nested_items.description: The values to match with the email's verdict using the given operator. For the EQUALS operator, if multiple values are given, the condition is deemed to match if any of the given verdicts match that of the email. For the NOT_EQUALS operator, if multiple values are given, the condition is deemed to match of none of the given verdicts match the verdict of the email.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The user-friendly name of the rule.

nested_items.name: Unless
nested_items.description: The 'unless conditions' of this rule. None of the conditions can match the email for the actions to be executed. If any of these conditions do match the email, then the actions are not executed.
